Finsweet List Nest — Stale Content on One Card
Symptom
One CMS card consistently shows wrong/old nested list content after republishing. All other cards update correctly. Works fine in incognito.
Root Causes (in order of likelihood)

Chrome browser cache storing stale fetched template page content
Finsweet List Nest default caching (persists until site republish)
Duplicate CMS item slug causing List Nest to fetch the wrong template page

Fixes
Immediate — force Chrome to clear cache:
Open DevTools (Cmd+Option+I) → right-click the reload button → "Empty Cache and Hard Reload" (only visible while DevTools is open)
Disable Finsweet cache (useful during active CMS development):
Add fs-list-cache="false" to the Collection List element that has fs-list-element="list"
If wrong content persists after cache clear:
Check the offending CMS item for a duplicate slug — inspect the fs-list-element="item-link" href on the live site to confirm it's pointing to the correct template page URL
Notes

List Nest works by fetching each item's Collection Template page — anything that causes the wrong URL to be fetched will pull wrong nested content
Hard refresh (Cmd+Shift+R) alone won't fix it — Chrome's cache must be fully emptied
Incognito always works because it has no prior cache